		<p>This is Simple PHP Comment System in PHP &amp; MySQL. We are going to create the PHP comment system with these functionalities. First of all, we are going to create comments database table. Then we will work inserting comments through comment form. Then we will create a few admin pages to moderate comments such as publish, edit &amp; update, delete existing comments. This will be built from the scratch with simple PHP &amp; MySQL.</p>
<h3>1. Create a Database Table</h3>
<p>Create a database with any name, but create a database table named comments with the following columns. </p>
<ul>
<li><strong>ID</strong> is integer type &amp; autoincreement</li>
<li><strong>Name</strong> is varchar type, it is used to store name field from comment form.</li>
<li><strong>E-Mail</strong> is varchar type, it is used to store the email from comment form.</li>
<li><strong>Subject</strong> is varchar type, it is used to store the comment text from comment form.</li>
<li><strong>Submittime</strong> is datetime type, it is used to store the time of comment submission by setting default to current_timestamp.</li>
<li><strong>Status</strong> is also varchar, it is used to store the status of comment. That is comment is published or not.</li>
</ul>


